      <acqinfo encodinganalog="541">
         <head>Provenance</head>
         <p> The papers of George Horace Gallup, statistician and author, were
		  given to the Library of Congress by Gallup between 1964 and 1980. Additions
		  were given by Rita Sappenfield between 1968 and 1969, and by Susan Thompson in
		  1979.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <processinfo encodinganalog="583">
         <head>Processing History</head>
         <p>The papers of George Horace Gallup were arranged and described in
		  1979. The finding aid was revised in 2007.</p>
      </processinfo>
