      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of George Horace Gallup (1901-1984) span the years
		  1936-1979, with the bulk of the material dating from 1960 to 1979. The
		  collection consists of speeches by Gallup, drafts of his books, and Gallup Poll
		  press releases from 1979. Final copies of the speeches are contained in bound
		  volumes accompanied by loose drafts and notes. The book file consists of drafts
		  of three unpublished works, on American foreign policy, the Vietnam War, and
		  public opinion surveys, and one published work.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
         <head>Arrangement of the Papers</head>
         <p>Bound speeches are arranged chronologically and loose drafts
		  alphabetically by title. The book file is arranged alphabetically by title.</p>
      </arrangement>
